<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="1596" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1596">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 701.5212/38.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Willard</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-13">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 13, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>56. Señor Azcona, Carranza’s diplomatic representative here, has just
                                presented to Minister of State an explanation of Caso incident and I
                                am informed that the Spanish Government has accepted same and, as
                                therein suggested, will send to Mexico confidential agent.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Willard</hi>.</signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>